<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-182-218  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 182 218.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Feb 19 1990 v24 n8 p133(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Taking a 4GL for a test drive; buying one calls for checking outits levels of comfort, speed and power. (fourth generationlanguages)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Keyes, Jessica.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Fourth-generation languages (4GLs) are even more appealing today,since the advent of bigger and more powerful processors and linksto microcomputers and workstations.andP;  These intuitive languages arenonprocedural and can be used by end users or information systemsprofessionals.andP;  Users looking for a 4GL need to consider suchthings as user-friendliness and whether the language isinterpretive or if it can be compiled.andP;  Many 4GLs includeanalytical features, such as cluster analysis, graphics charting,time-series analysis and regression analysis.andP;  Users need to knowhow a 4GL transfers data from a mainframe to a microcomputer, andwhether such a transfer requires the installation of additionalsoftware.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Fourth-Generation LanguagesSoftware SelectionUser-Friendliness.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>